SEC. 8.

Incentives to a Pioneer Enterprise.

âIn addition to the incentives provided in the preceding section, pioneer enterprises shall be granted the following incentives benefits:

(a)

Tax Exemptions.

âExemption from all taxes under the National Internal Revenue Code, except income tax, to the following extent:

(1) One hundred per cent up to December 31, 1972;

(2) Seventy-five per cent up to December 31, 1975;

(3) Fifty per cent up to December 31, 1977;

(4) Twenty per cent up to December 31, 1979;

(5) Ten per cent up to December 31, 1981.

